Princess Maria Czartoryska, also formerly known as Duchess Maria , Duchess Louis of Württemberg (15 March 1768, Warsaw – 21 October 1854, Paris), was a Polish noble, writer, musician and philanthropist.
In 1782 she moved with her parents to Puławy.
Since 1784 to 1793 Maria was married to Duke Louis of Württemberg, who became the Hetman of the Lithuanian Army in the 1792 war against Russia.

Following her divorce, Maria lived mostly in Warsaw, and since 1798 to 1804 spent winters in Vienna and summers at Puławy.
In 1816 she published Malvina, or the Heart's Intuition, considered Poland's first psychological novel.
In 1837 she moved to Paris, where she lived with her brother, Adam Jerzy Czartoryski.
